events.name: Denver Nuggets at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 32 points and had 11 rebounds in just 27 minutes, leading the Denver Nuggets over the New York Knicks 113-99 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic gets 32 points in just 27 minutes, Nuggets rout Knicks

headlines.description: — The Bulls were down, but not out.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, DeRozan lead Bulls to 111-107 win over Nets

headlines.description: — It wasn’t exactly a revenge game for the Milwaukee Bucks, though it felt good.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks rout short-handed Heat 124-102 without Antetokounmpo

headlines.description: — The next time the Memphis Grizzlies trail in what is expected to be about two weeks without Ja Morant will be the first.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies hang on to beat Mavericks 97-90 after 73-point win

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Derrick White scored 25 points, Dejounte Murray had 22 points and 12 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs held off a furious rally to beat the Golden State Warriors 112-107 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs withstand Warriors' rally for 112-107 victory

events.name: Boston Celtics at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Terence Davis scored 23 of his 28 points in the second half and the Sacramento Kings beat the Los Angeles Clippers for the second time in four nights with a 104-99 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis’ 28 lead Kings to 2nd straight win over Clippers
